This paper is about word sense induction, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a new model called AutoSense to solve the problem of sense granularity flexibility in WSI. This involves using latent variable models and topic modeling techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also involves artificial intelligence (AI) techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper involves neural networks, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
